text.section:
Except for the ex officio members or their designees:
The term of a member is 4 years;
The terms of members are staggered as required by the terms provided for members of the Board on July 1, 1985;
At the end of a term, a member continues to serve until a successor is appointed and qualifies;
A member who is appointed after a term is begun serves for the rest of the term and until a successor is appointed and qualifies; and
A member may serve no more than 2 terms.
